# Trivy ignore list for the published container image.
#
# Keep in sync with .cargo/audit.toml -- same reachability reasoning applies:
# rsa's vulnerable private-key timing path is never exercised by this service.
# The distroless runtime image ships only the compiled binary (no Cargo.lock),
# so Trivy's Rust-crate scanning wouldn't normally surface this; listed here
# so the scan gate stays green if that ever changes.
RUSTSEC-2023-0071
CVE-2023-49092
